        * html/HTMLInputElement.h: (CyberCore::HTMLInputElement::cacheSelection): Added.
        * html/HTMLInputElement.cpp:
        (CyberCore::HTMLInputElement::init): Initializes cached selection.
        (CyberCore::HTMLInputElement::selectionStart): If this element doesn't have focus, return the cached selection value.
        (CyberCore::HTMLInputElement::selectionEnd): ditto.
        (CyberCore::HTMLInputElement::setValue): Restore a caret at the starting point of the old selection.  Matches Safari 2.0 behavior.

        * html/HTMLTextAreaElement.h: (CyberCore::HTMLTextAreaElement::cacheSelection): Added.
        * html/HTMLTextAreaElement.cpp:
        (CyberCore::HTMLTextAreaElement::HTMLTextAreaElement): Initializes cached selection.
        (CyberCore::HTMLTextAreaElement::selectionStart): If this element doesn't have focus, return the cached selection value.
        (CyberCore::HTMLTextAreaElement::selectionEnd): ditto.
        (CyberCore::HTMLTextAreaElement::focus): If this is the first focus, set a caret at the end of the text.  Otherwise,
        restore the cached selection.  This matches other browsers' behavior.
        (CyberCore::HTMLTextAreaElement::setValue): Restore a caret at the starting point of the old selection.  Matches Safari 2.0 behavior.

        * page/Frame.h: Added notifyRendererOfSelectionChange method. 
        * page/Frame.cpp:
        (CyberCore::Frame::notifyRendererOfSelectionChange): Added.  Calls selectionChanged for text fields and textareas.  Forwards a userTriggered
        argument so selectionChanged knows whether or not to fire onSelect.
        (CyberCore::Frame::setSelection): Calls notifyRendererOfSelectionChange(false).  This gets called for all selection changes, so the renderer
        can always update its cached selection values.
        (CyberCore::Frame::handleMouseReleaseEvent): Calls notifyRendererOfSelectionChange(true) so onSelect will get fired when the user is done
        making a selection with the mouse.
        * bridge/mac/CyberCoreFrameBridge.mm:
        (-[CyberCoreFrameBridge alterCurrentSelection:direction:granularity:]): Calls notifyRendererOfSelectionChange(true) so onSelect gets
        fired when the user makes a selection with the keyboard.
